	-- CAINGORN
	('en_US',	'LOC_CIVILIZATION_IPG_CAINGORN_MINOR_NAME',			'Caingorn'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_CITY_NAME_IPG_CAINGORN_MINOR',					'Caingorn'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_CIVILIZATION_IPG_CAINGORN_MINOR_DESCRIPTION',	'Caingorn city-state'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_CIVILIZATION_IPG_CAINGORN_MINOR_ADJECTIVE',		'Caingornese'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_MINOR_CIV_IPG_CAINGORN_MINOR_TRAIT_NAME',		'Caingorn Suzerain Bonus'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_MINOR_CIV_IPG_CAINGORN_MINOR_TRAIT_DESCRIPTION',
	'Receive the [ICON_RESOURCE_IPG_DRAGON] Golden Dragon Scales Luxury resource. This cannot be earned any other way in the game, and provides 12 [ICON_Amenities] Amenities.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][COLOR_FLOAT_MILITARY]If you are also Suzerain of any Militaristic city-state[ENDCOLOR]: +1 [ICON_Amenities] Amenity for cities with a garrisoned unit.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][COLOR_FLOAT_FAITH]If you are also Suzerain of any Religious city-state[ENDCOLOR]: +5% [ICON_Faith] Faith in Happy cities.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][COLOR_FLOAT_PRODUCTION]If you are also Suzerain of any Industrial city-state[ENDCOLOR]: +5% [ICON_Production] Production in Happy cities.'),

	('en_US',	'LOC_PEDIA_CITYSTATES_PAGE_CIVILIZATION_IPG_CAINGORN_MINOR_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1',
	'Caingorn is part of the Hengfors League and the ruler member, and lies west of the Kestrel Mountains. The Braa forms a natural border with Malleore.'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_PEDIA_CITYSTATES_PAGE_CIVILIZATION_IPG_CAINGORN_MINOR_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_2',
	'The kingdom was part of the East March in Kovir, but is now allied with Creyden and Malleore, forming the League. After the First Treaty of Lan Exeter, Benda of Kaedwen was allowed to use, in official documents, the title of sovereign of Caingorn and Malleore. Currently, Caingorn is ruled by King Niedamir.'),
	
	-- MALLEORE
	('en_US',	'LOC_CIVILIZATION_IPG_MALLEORE_MINOR_NAME',			'Malleore'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_CITY_NAME_IPG_MALLEORE_MINOR',					'Malleore'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_CIVILIZATION_IPG_MALLEORE_MINOR_DESCRIPTION',	'Malleore city-state'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_CIVILIZATION_IPG_MALLEORE_MINOR_ADJECTIVE',		'Malleorean'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_MINOR_CIV_IPG_MALLEORE_MINOR_TRAIT_NAME',		'Malleore Suzerain Bonus'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_MINOR_CIV_IPG_MALLEORE_MINOR_TRAIT_DESCRIPTION',
	'Open Borders with all city-states, and +2 Influence points per turn toward earning [ICON_Envoy] Envoys.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][COLOR_FLOAT_CULTURE]If you are also Suzerain of any Cultural city-state[ENDCOLOR]: +5% [ICON_Culture] Culture in Happy cities.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][COLOR_FLOAT_FAITH]If you are also Suzerain of any Religious city-state[ENDCOLOR]: +5% [ICON_Faith] Faith in Happy cities.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][COLOR_FLOAT_PRODUCTION]If you are also Suzerain of any Industrial city-state[ENDCOLOR]: +5% [ICON_Production] Production in Happy cities.'),

	('en_US',	'LOC_PEDIA_CITYSTATES_PAGE_CIVILIZATION_IPG_MALLEORE_MINOR_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1',
	'Malleore is a northern region formerly part of the East March of Kovir and now a principality of Hengfors League. It is located in the foothills of the Dragon Mountains. The nearest major city is Hengfors.'),

	-- BAREFIELD
	('en_US',	'LOC_CIVILIZATION_IPG_BAREFIELD_MINOR_NAME',			'Barefield'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_CITY_NAME_IPG_BAREFIELD_MINOR',					'Barefield'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_CIVILIZATION_IPG_BAREFIELD_MINOR_DESCRIPTION',	'Barefield city-state'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_CIVILIZATION_IPG_BAREFIELD_MINOR_ADJECTIVE',		'Barefielder'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_MINOR_CIV_IPG_BAREFIELD_MINOR_TRAIT_NAME',		'Barefield Suzerain Bonus'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_MINOR_CIV_IPG_BAREFIELD_MINOR_TRAIT_DESCRIPTION',
	'+1 [ICON_Faith] Faith from Monuments, and +1 [ICON_Faith] Faith more in cities at maximum Loyalty.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][COLOR_FLOAT_CULTURE]If you are also Suzerain of any Cultural city-state[ENDCOLOR]: +5% [ICON_Culture] Culture in Happy cities.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][COLOR_FLOAT_MILITARY]If you are also Suzerain of any Militaristic city-state[ENDCOLOR]: +1 [ICON_Amenities] Amenity for cities with a garrisoned unit.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][COLOR_FLOAT_PRODUCTION]If you are also Suzerain of any Industrial city-state[ENDCOLOR]: +5% [ICON_Production] Production in Happy cities.'),

	('en_US',	'LOC_PEDIA_CITYSTATES_PAGE_CIVILIZATION_IPG_BAREFIELD_MINOR_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1',
	'Barefield (Polish: Ho≈Çopole, also translated as Woefield in The World of the Witcher), is a northern free city-state protected by it own militia. It''s a minor land which is part of the former East March along with Malleore, Creyden, and Caingorn. It borders Kaedwen and is walled in by the Kestrel Mountains to the east and the river Braa. There''s a temple of Kreve in the center of the city.'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_PEDIA_CITYSTATES_PAGE_CIVILIZATION_IPG_BAREFIELD_MINOR_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_2',
	'The short story "The Bounds of Reason" partly takes place in Barefield.'),
	
	-- CREYDEN
	('en_US',	'LOC_CIVILIZATION_IPG_CREYDEN_MINOR_NAME',			'Creyden'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_CITY_NAME_IPG_CREYDEN_MINOR',					'Creyden'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_CIVILIZATION_IPG_CREYDEN_MINOR_DESCRIPTION',	'Creyden city-state'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_CIVILIZATION_IPG_CREYDEN_MINOR_ADJECTIVE',		'Creydenian'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_MINOR_CIV_IPG_CREYDEN_MINOR_TRAIT_NAME',		'Creyden Suzerain Bonus'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_MINOR_CIV_IPG_CREYDEN_MINOR_TRAIT_DESCRIPTION',	'+1 [ICON_Production] Production and +1 [ICON_Gold] Gold from Pastures, doubled if placed on a Bonus Resource.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][COLOR_FLOAT_CULTURE]If you are also Suzerain of any Cultural city-state[ENDCOLOR]: +5% [ICON_Culture] Culture in Happy cities.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][COLOR_FLOAT_MILITARY]If you are also Suzerain of any Militaristic city-state[ENDCOLOR]: +1 [ICON_Amenities] Amenity for cities with a garrisoned unit.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE][COLOR_FLOAT_FAITH]If you are also Suzerain of any Religious city-state[ENDCOLOR]: +5% [ICON_Faith] Faith in Happy cities.'),

	('en_US',	'LOC_PEDIA_CITYSTATES_PAGE_CIVILIZATION_IPG_CREYDEN_MINOR_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1',
	'Creyden is a small northern principality, vassal to Kovir and Poviss and member of the Hengfors League. It was conquered by the Earldom of Kovir prior to the 12th century, and was likely part of the East March.'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_PEDIA_CITYSTATES_PAGE_CIVILIZATION_IPG_CREYDEN_MINOR_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_2',
	'At some point in the 1250s, King Niedamir conquered Creyden. This deed disturbed the newly crowned Esterad Thyssen of Kovir and Poviss because Creyden had been a Kovirian vassal for ages. After a short war the Fourth Treaty of Lan Exeter was signed, and while Creyden remained part of Hengfors League, it was granted to Esterad''s young daughter Gaudemunda and was governed by Esterad himself until she reached maturity. Gaudemunda later married Prince Aristide Vermuellen and the Vermuellens were still in power in 1352 when Gaudemunda and Aristide''s son, Guiscard, was 95 years old.'),
	('en_US',	'LOC_PEDIA_CITYSTATES_PAGE_CIVILIZATION_IPG_CREYDEN_MINOR_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_3',
	'The majority of Creyden is situated on a limestone bedrock with only a shallow layer of soil, especially in the west. Its landscape consists mostly of vast, lush meadows spotted with rocky outcrops here and there. Due to the poor soil, the duchy is not economically strong, living mostly off sheep farms. It exports wool and imports oversea goods such as batiste.');